  "name": "Wildflowers of California",
  "description": "A field guide to 30 beloved California wildflowers — from the golden poppies of spring hillsides to the desert lilies of the Mojave. Each flower is a doorway into California's extraordinary ecological diversity, with tiered content for young children (Story) and older readers (Science). Organized by habitat: coast, valley, foothill, mountain, and desert.\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Mary Elizabeth Parsons' 'The Wild Flowers of California' (1897, Cunningham, Curtiss & Welch) with illustrations by Margaret Warriner Buck — delicate, accurate botanical line drawings. Albert Kellogg (1813–1887), founding member of the California Academy of Sciences, botanical illustrations of California flora.",
